and minimize the stop band ripple <m:math><m:msub><m:mi>δ</m:mi><m:mi>s</m:mi></m:msub></m:math>. A problem with convergence
occurs if one of the <m:math><m:mi>δ</m:mi></m:math>'s becomes negative during the iterations. A
modification to the basic exchange has been developed to give reliable
convergence <link target-id="bid56"/>.</para>
